encies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"TypeScript's [conditional types](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/advanced-types.html#conditional-types) suit the behaviour of a lot of legacy code.\r\n\r\nProposed syntax:\r\n\r\n`(<template param> is <union type> ? <union type> : <union type>)`\r\n\r\nEnforcing brackets makes parsing for this a lot easier.\r\n\r\nIn use:\r\n\r\n```php\r\nclass A {\r\n    /** @var array<string, string> */\r\n    private array $itemAttr = [];\r\n    \r\n    /**\r\n     * @template T as ?string\r\n     * @param T $name\r\n     * @return string|string[]\r\n     * @psalm-return (T is string ? string : array<string, string>)\r\n     */\r\n    public function getAttribute(?string $name, string $default = '')\r\n    {\r\n       if (null === $name) {\r\n            return $this->itemAttr;\r\n        }\r\n        return isset($this->itemAttr[$name]) ? $this->itemAttr[$name] : $default;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n(new A)->getAttribute(\"colour\", \"red\"); // typed as string\r\n(new A)->getAttribute(null); // typed as array<string, string>\r\n(new A)->getAttribute($_GET[\"foo\"]); // typed as string|array<string, string>\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"muglug","id":2292638,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyOTI2Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2292638?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug","html_url":"https://github.com/muglug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/events{/priva